{"title_page": "5 Seconds of Summer discography", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist       = [[5 Seconds of Summer]]\n| Image        = 5 Seconds of Summer at Enmore Theatre, Sydney, 30.04.14.jpg\n| Caption      = 5 Seconds of Summer performing at the [[Enmore Theatre]] in Sydney, Australia on 30 April 2014\n| Studio       = 4\n| Live         = 2\n| EP           = 7\n| Soundtrack   = \n| Video        = \n| Music videos = 23\n| Singles      = 21\n| B-sides      = 7\n| 1Option      = 4\n| 1Option name = Promotional singles\n}}\n\nAustralian [[pop rock]] band [[5 Seconds of Summer]] have released four [[studio album]]s, two live albums, seven [[extended play]]s, 21 [[Single (music)|singles]], four [[promotional single]]s, and 23 [[music video]]s. All four of their studio albums debuted at number one in Australia and their first three albums debuted at number one in the United States. All the singles from their studio albums charted in several countries.\n\nOn 5 February 2014, 5 Seconds of Summer listed their worldwide debut single \"[[She Looks So Perfect]]\" for pre-order on the [[iTunes Store]]. In late March 2014, \"She Looks So Perfect\" was released in the UK, their most successful single to date. It debuted at number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]], making 5 Seconds of Summer the fourth Australian band to have a number one song in the UK and the first in 14 years. On 9 April 2014, the ''She Looks So Perfect'' EP debuted at number two on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]].\n\nOn 13 May 2014, the band announced their debut album, named ''[[5 Seconds of Summer (album)|5 Seconds of Summer]]'', which was released on 22 July 2014.<ref name=\"iTunes 5 Seconds of Summer\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/5-seconds-of-summer-deluxe/id876374888|title=iTunes \u2013 Music \u2013 5 Seconds of Summer by 5 Seconds of Summer|publisher=[[iTunes Store]] (Australia). [[Apple Inc.|Apple]]|accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref> It debuted at number one in Australia and the US. Their second single \"[[Don't Stop (5 Seconds of Summer song)|Don't Stop]]\" was released in June and debuted at number one in Ireland, number two in the UK and number 8 in New Zealand. On 15 July 2014, they released \"[[Amnesia (5 Seconds of Summer song)|Amnesia]]\" as the third single from the album. It peaked at number three in Ireland, number seven in the UK and number sixteen in the US. The band released \"[[Good Girls (5 Seconds of Summer song)|Good Girls]]\" as the final single from the album. It peaked at number twelve in Ireland and number nineteen in the UK.\n\nOn 21 November 2014, the band announced their first live album, ''[[LiveSOS]]'', which was released on 15 December 2014. It peaked at number seven in Australia and number thirteen in the US.  The band released \"[[What I Like About You (song)#5 Seconds of Summer version|What I Like About You]]\" as a single from the album. It peaked at number 137 in the UK.\n\nOn 17 July 2015, the band released \"[[She's Kinda Hot]]\", the first single off their second studio album, ''[[Sounds Good Feels Good]]''. It peaked at number six in Australia, number seven in Ireland, number fourteen in the UK, and number twenty-two in the US. The band released \"[[Hey Everybody!]]\" as the second single from the album on 9 October 2015. It peaked at number forty-nine in the UK and Ireland and number seventy in Australia. The band then released ''Sounds Good Feels Good'' two weeks later. It peaked at number one in the charts of ten countries, including Australia, Canada, Ireland, the UK and the US. The band released \"[[Jet Black Heart]]\" as the third and final single from the album. It peaked at number thirty-four in Australia, number sixty in the UK, number seventy-eight in Ireland and number ninety-five in the US.\n\nOn 22 February 2018, the band released \"[[Want You Back (5 Seconds of Summer song)|Want You Back]]\", the lead single from their third studio album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8214818/5-seconds-of-summer-want-you-back-announces-2018-tour|accessdate=29 July 2018|title=5 Seconds of Summer Releases New Single 'Want You Back,' Announces 2018 Tour|website=Billboard}}</ref> It peaked in the top 40 in the UK, Ireland, and Australia. The second single was the [[Youngblood (5 Seconds of Summer song)|title track]], which peaked at number one for eight consecutive weeks in Australia and four consecutive weeks in New Zealand. On 15 June 2018, the band released their third studio album ''[[Youngblood (5 Seconds of Summer album)|Youngblood]]''.<ref name=\"5 Seconds of Summer Fans Are Totally Losing It Over 'Youngblood'\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8461165/5-seconds-of-summer-youngblood-album-fans-freaking-out-excited|accessdate=29 July 2018|website=Billboard|title=5 Seconds of Summer Fans Are Totally Losing It Over 'Youngblood'}}</ref> It debuted at number one in Australia<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/2018/youngblood-gives-5sos-third-1-album|accessdate= 29 July 2018|website=ARIA Charts|title=Youngblood gives 5SOS third #1 album}}</ref> and the US.<ref name=\"5 Seconds of Summer Fans Are Totally Losing It Over 'Youngblood'\" />\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br/><ref name=\"AUS\">{{cite web|url=http://australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=5+Seconds+Of+Summer|title=Discography 5 Seconds of Summer|website=australian-charts.com}}\n* \"Money\": {{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/aria-singles-justin-bieber-maintains-top-spot-after-four-weeks-20150926|title=ARIA Singles: Justin Bieber Maintains Top Spot After Four Weeks|publisher=Noise11|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|date=26 September 2015|accessdate=26 September 2015}}\n* \"Hey Everybody!\": {{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/aria-singles-macklemore-ryan-lewis-downtown-spends-another-week-at-no-1-20151017|title=ARIA Singles: Macklemore & Ryan Lewis 'Downtown' Spends Another Week at No 1|publisher=Noise11|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|date=17 October 2015|accessdate=17 October 2015}}\n* \"Valentine\": {{cite web|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2018/9/aria-chart-watch-491/|title=ARIA Chart Watch #491|publisher=auspOp|date=22 September 2018|accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL]]<br/><ref name=\"VL\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=5+Seconds+Of+Summer|title=Discography 5 Seconds of Summer|publisher=Ultratop}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br/><ref name=\"CANAlbums\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/5-seconds-of-summer/chart-history/canadian-albums|title=5 Seconds of Summer Chart History: Billboard Canadian Albums Chart|website=Billboard|accessdate=27 June 2018|location=United States}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Hitlisten|DEN]]<br/><ref name=\"DEN\">{{cite web|url=http://danishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=5+Seconds+Of+Summer|title=Discography 5 Seconds of Summer|website=danishcharts.dk|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br/><ref name=\"FRA\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Irish Albums Chart|IRE]]<br/><ref name=\"IRE\">{{cite web|url=http://irish-char