ws/desktop/bb776899%28v=vs.85%29.aspx User Environment Variables]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180511150138/https://www.setx.cc/ fix setx.exe not found bug]\n\n{{Unix commands}}\n{{Windows commands}}\n\n[[Category:Operating system technology]]\n[[Category:Environment variables]]\n", "name_user": "Tijmen Wil", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eWindows:Add links to doses", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Environment_variable"}
{"title_page": "Li Yong-ju", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|birth_date=\n|death_date=\n|nationality=North Korean\n|occupation=Military officer, politician\n|birth_place=[[Korea under Japanese rule|Japanese Korea]]\n|education = \n|party= [[Workers' Party of Korea]]\n|nationality = [[Korean people|Korean]]\n|citizenship = [[Citizenship in North Korea|North Korean]]\n|allegiance   = {{flag|North Korea|1948}}\n|branch       = {{armed forces|North Korea}}\n|serviceyears = \n|rank         =  [[image:Fleet Admiral rank insignia (North Korea).svg|25px]] [[Daejang|Admiral]]\n}}\nLi Yong-ju ({{lang-ko|\ub9ac\uc6a9\uc8fc}}) is an Admiral and politician of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea ([[North Korea]]) and a candidate member of the [[Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea|Central Committee]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]]. He was member of the [[2009 North Korean parliamentary election|12th convocation]] of the [[Supreme People's Assembly]]. He is currently the commander of the [[Korean People's Navy]].<ref>[http://www.nocutnews.co.kr/news/4458651 \u201c\u5317 \ub9ac\uc6a9\uc8fc \ud574\uad70\uc0ac\ub839\uad00, \ub300\uc7a5\uc73c\ub85c \uc2b9\uc9c4\u201d. 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 14\uc77c\uc5d0 \ud655\uc778\ud568.]</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nAfter being promoted to Lieutenant General, he served as a delegate to the 12th Supreme People's Assembly in March 2009 as representative of the 548th [[electoral district]]. He served as a candidate member of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and in March 2014, as representative of the [[2014 North Korean parliamentary election|13th convocation]] of the Supreme People's Assembly for the District 449. In December 2011 he participated at the funeral committee which [[Death and Funeral of Kim Jong-il|organized the funeral]] of Kim Jong-il.<ref>[http://www.ohmynews.com/NWS_Web/View/at_pg.aspx?CNTN_CD=A0001672651]</ref>\n\nIn April 2015, he succeeded [[Kim Myong-sik (politician)|Kim Myong-sik]] as the Navy commander. In August, he was promoted to admiral, and in April 2016, he became a member of the Central Committee of the Korean Workers' Party.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Kim Myong-sik (politician)|Kim Myong-sik]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Commander of the [[Korean People's Navy]]|years=2014-current}}\n{{s-aft|after=incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{North Korean generals}}\n\n[[Category:Members of the Supreme People's Assembly]]\n[[Category:North Korean generals]]\n[[Category:Workers' Party of Korea politicians]]\n[[Category:Admirals]]\n\n[[ko:\ub9ac\uc6a9\uc8fc]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|birth_date=\n|death_date=\n|nationality=North Korean\n|occupation=Military officer, politician\n|birth_place=[[Korea under Japanese rule|Japanese Korea]]\n|education = \n|party= [[Workers' Party of Korea]]\n|nationality = [[Korean people|Korean]]\n|citizenship = [[Citizenship in North Korea|North Korean]]\n|allegiance   = {{flag|North Korea|1948}}\n|branch       = {{armed forces|North Korea}}\n|serviceyears = \n|rank         =  [[image:Fleet Admiral rank insignia (North Korea).svg|25px]] [[Daejang|Admiral]]\n}}\nLi Yong-ju ({{lang-ko|\ub9ac\uc6a9\uc8fc}}) is an Admiral and politician of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea ([[North Korea]]) and a candidate member of the [[Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea|Central Committee]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]]. He was member of the [[2009 North Korean parliamentary election|12th convocation]] of the [[Supreme People's Assembly]]. He is currently the commander of the [[Korean People's Navy]].<ref>[http://www.nocutnews.co.kr/news/4458651 \u201c\u5317 \ub9ac\uc6a9\uc8fc \ud574\uad70\uc0ac\ub839\uad00, \ub300\uc7a5\uc73c\ub85c \uc2b9\uc9c4\u201d. 2018\ub144 8\uc6d4 14\uc77c\uc5d0 \ud655\uc778\ud568.]</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nAfter being promoted to Lieutenant General, he served as a delegate to the 12th Supreme People's Assembly in March 2009 as representative of the 548th [[electoral district]]. He served as a candidate member of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and in March 2014, as representative of the [[2014 North Korean parliamentary election|13th convocation]] of the Supreme People's Assembly for the District 449. In December 2011 he participated at the funeral committee which [[Death and Funeral of Kim Jong-il|organized the funeral]] of Kim Jong-il.<ref>[http://www.ohmynews.com/NWS_Web/View/at_pg.aspx?CNTN_CD=A0001672651]</ref>\n\nIn April 2015, he succeeded [[Kim Myong-sik]] as the Navy commander. In August, he was promoted to admiral, and in April 2016, he became a member of the Central Committee of the Korean Workers' Party.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Kim Myong-sik (politician)|Kim Myong-sik]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Commander of the [[Korean People's Navy]]|years=2014-current}}\n{{s-aft|after=incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{North Korean generals}}\n\n[[Category:Members of the Supreme People's Assembly]]\n[[Category:North Korean generals]]\n[[Category:Workers' Party of Korea politicians]]\n[[Category:Admirals]]\n\n[[ko:\ub9ac\uc6a9\uc8fc]]\n", "name_user": "Tassedethe", "label": "safe", "comment": "v2.02 - Repaired 1 link to disambiguation page -(You can help)-Kim Myong-sik", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Li_Yong-ju"}
{"title_page": "Myrat Anna\u00fdew", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Myrat Anna\u00fdew\n| fullname = \n| image = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1993|5|6}}\n| birth_place = [[A\u015fgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]]\n| height = 1.77m\n| currentclub = [[Altyn Asyr FK]]<ref>[https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/myrat-annayew/51508/]</ref>\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| years1 = 2015\u20132017\n| clubs1 = [[Altyn Asyr FK|Altyn Asyr]]\n| years2 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs2 = [[Ahal FK|Ahal]]\n| caps1 = \n| goals1 = \n| years3 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs3 = [[Altyn Asyr FK|Altyn Asyr]]\n| nationalyears1 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| manageryears1 = \n| managerclubs1 = \n| pcupdate = 13 January 2019\n| ntupdate = 13 January 2019\n}}\n\n'''Myrat Anna\u00fdew''' (born 6 May 1993) is a [[Turkmenistan|Turkmen]] professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Altyn Asyr FK|Altyn Asyr]]<ref>[https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/myrat-annayew/51508/]</ref> and [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]] as [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\n==International career==\nAnna\u00fdew made his senior debut for [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]] against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]], where he also scored his first international goal. He was included in [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]]'s squad for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]] in the United Arab Emirates.<ref name=\"AFC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.the-afc.com/afc/documents/PdfFiles/afc-asian-cup-uae-2019-complete-squad-lists |title=AFC Asian Cup UAE 2019 Complete Squad Lists |website=The-AFC.com |publisher=[[Asian Football Confederation]] |format=PDF |date=27 December 2018 |access-date=2 January 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228174458/http://www.the-afc.com/afc/documents/PdfFiles/afc-asian-cup-uae-2019-complete-squad-lists |archive-date=28 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe played for [[Turkmenistan national futsal team]] at [[2020 AFC Futsal Championship qualification]].<ref>[http://stats.the-afc.com/match_report/16312]</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International===\n''Statistics accurate as of match played 13 January 2019''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=3|[[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2018||4||0\n|-\n|2018||1||0\n|-\n!Total||5||0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{WorldFootball.net|myrat-annayew}}\n* {{NFT player|68678}}\n\n{{Turkmenistan squad 2019 AFC Asian Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Annayew, Myrat}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Turkmenistan footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Turkmenistan international footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Ahal players]]\n[[Category:2019 AFC Asian Cup players]]\n[[Category:Men's futsal players]]\n\n{{Turkmenistan-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Myrat Anna\u00fdew\n| fullname = \n| image = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1993|5|6}}\n| birth_place = [[A\u015fgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]]\n| height = 1.77m\n| currentclub = [[Altyn Asyr FK]]<ref>[https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/myrat-annayew/51508/]</ref>\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| years1 = 2015\u20132017\n| clubs1 = [[Altyn Asyr FK|Altyn Asyr]]\n| years2 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs2 = [[Ahal FK|Ahal]]\n| caps1 = \n| goals1 = \n| years3 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs3 = [[Altyn Asyr FK|Altyn Asyr]]\n| nationalyears1 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| manageryears1 = \n| managerclubs1 = \n| pcupdate = 13 January 2019\n| ntupdate = 13 January 2019\n}}\n\n'''Myrat Anna\u00fdew''' (born 6 May 1993) is a [[Turkmenistan|Turkmen]] professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Altyn Asyr FK|Altyn Asyr]]<ref>[https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/myrat-annayew/51508/]</ref> and [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]] as [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\n==International career==\nAnna\u00fdew made his senior debut for [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]] against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]], where he also scored his first international goal. He was included in [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]]'s squad for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]] in the United Arab Emirates.<ref name=\"AFC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.the-afc.com/afc/documents/PdfFiles/afc-asian-cup-uae-2019-complete-squad-lists |title=AFC Asian Cup UAE 2019 Complete Squad Lists |website=The-AFC.com |publisher=[[Asian Football Confederation]] |format=PDF |date=27 December 2018 |access-date=2 January 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228174458/http://www.the-afc.com/afc/documents/PdfFiles/afc-asian-cup-uae-2019-complete-squad-lists |archive-date=28 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe played for [[Turkmenistan national futsal team]] at [[2020 AFC Futsal Championship qualification]].<ref>[http://stats.the-afc.com/match_report/16312]</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International===\n''Statistics accurate as of match played 13 January 2019''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!colspan=3|[[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2018||4||0\n|-\n|2018||1||0\n|-\n!Total||5||0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{WorldFootball.net|gueycmyrat-annagulyyew}}\n* {{NFT player|68678}}\n\n{{Turkmenistan squad 2019 AFC Asian Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Annayew, Myrat}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Turkmenistan footba